                <Header>Freedom of Information Act (FOIA)</Header>
                <Paragraph>To any person, the FOIA gives a statutory right for obtaining access to Government information in the records of executive branch agencies. This right to access is limited, however, when the requested information is shielded from disclosure by one or more of nine exemptions that are contained within the statute.</Paragraph>
